"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Lie on a bed or the floor. Bend the \"good\" knee and&nbsp;place the foot on the floor. Keep the injured leg straight. On the injured side, tighten the quadriceps, keep the&nbsp;knee straight, and lift the leg about 18 inches (45 cm)&nbsp;off the floor. Slowly lower the leg back to the bed or floor. Rest as needed. Repeat 10 to 15 times (one set). Perform a total of 3 sets.",
